# === Secrets / credentials — never commit ===
.env
*.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!*.env.example
**/auth.json
**/*token*
**/*secret*
**/*private*
id_rsa
id_ed25519
*.pem
*.key

# Onboarding files named "secret(s)" that contain NO secret values — only
# 1Password op:// references and documentation. Explicitly vetted + allowed.
!bin/setup-secrets.sh
!docs/onboarding-secrets.md

# Memory notes (memory/**/*.md) document things *about* credentials — incident
# records, access paths, rotation to-dos — so their filenames routinely contain
# "secret"/"token"/"private". The rules above match FILENAMES, not content, so
# they silently dropped exactly the notes most worth keeping (including a
# pending-rotation incident record that never reached the hub) while providing
# no real protection: a live key inside a normally-named .md sails through
# untouched. Memory is secret-free by policy and bin/ai-sync-memory gates on
# content. Scoped to *.md so a stray .env/.pem/.key under memory/ stays ignored.
!memory/**/*.md

# The secrets-to-1password skill: instructions only, no secret values. The
# `**/*secret*` rule above matches the DIRECTORY name, and git will not descend
# into an excluded directory — so the directory must be un-ignored before its
# contents can be. Without both lines, `git add` silently refuses the skill and
# it never reaches GitHub: that is exactly how this skill went missing once
# already, documented in five places but committed in none.
!skills/claude/secrets-to-1password/
!skills/claude/secrets-to-1password/**

# Trigger-eval prompt sets (tools/skill-trigger-eval): fabricated user prompts
# used to measure whether a skill fires. No secret values — deliberately, since
# a prompt only needs to *mention* a credential to test triggering. Here
# `**/*secret*` matches the FILENAME rather than the directory, so unlike the
# skill above a single file-level negation is enough.
!tools/skill-trigger-eval/*secret*.eval.json

# Per-run output from that tool — regenerated on every run, never worth tracking.
tools/skill-trigger-eval/*.results.json

# === OS / editor noise ===
.DS_Store
node_modules/

# === AI run/tmp artifacts (generated inside app repos, never here) ===
.ai/runs/
.ai/tmp/
.ai/reviews/

# === Machine-local AI permissions ===
.claude/settings.local.json

# Python bytecode from tools/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
